Metric: Order Conversion Rate
Description: Percentage of unique sessions that result in a completed order. Measures the effectiveness of the purchase funnel from product view through checkout completion. Excludes bot traffic and internal test accounts.
Owner: growth-analytics
Tags: conversion, funnel, ecommerce, growth

Source: orders, sessions

Given the session is from an identified non-bot visitor
  And the session occurred within the reporting period
  And internal test accounts are excluded
  And only the first order per session is counted

When we calculate
  Then count distinct sessions that produced at least one completed order
  And divide by the total distinct qualifying sessions
  And multiply by 100

The result is "Order Conversion Rate"

Trust:
  Freshness must be less than 1 hours
  Null rate on session_id must be less than 1%
  Null rate on status must be less than 0%
  Row count of orders must not drop more than 30% day over day
  Value must be between 0.1 and 25
  Value must not change more than 35% week over week
